&lt;/h1>
&lt;h2 class="relative group">Sanskrit Subhashitam PART1
&lt;div id="sanskrit-subhashitampart1" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#sanskrit-subhashitampart1" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>उद्यमेनैव सिध्यन्ति कार्याणि न मनोरथैः ।&lt;br>
न हि सुप्तस्य सिंहस्य प्रविशन्ति मुखे मृगाः ।।&lt;br>
Meaning: Success in life can be achieved only by hard work and not by merely wishing for it. No animal will enter into the mouth of a lion that is sleeping.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Samskrut Video Links</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/samskrutyatra/samskrut-video-links/</link><pubDate>Mon, 22 Jul 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/samskrutyatra/samskrut-video-links/</guid><description>&lt;p>
